## Severity
Minor
## Dimension
complexity
## Location
src/tools/bash/mod.rs:319-401
## Violation
`execute_bash` is 83 lines, branches on `run_in_background`, then again on `#[cfg(windows)]` vs `#[cfg(not(windows))]`, then constructs output, then truncates, then sets `is_error` from exit status. SRP violation — argument extraction, OS-specific spawn, output assembly, truncation, and error-mapping all live in one function. Cyclomatic complexity sits around 12.

Quoted (mod.rs:319-401, abridged):
```
pub fn execute_bash(args: &HashMap<String, Value>) -> (String, bool) {
    let Some(command) = args.get("command").and_then(|v| v.as_str()) else { ... };
    if let Err(msg) = validate_command(command) { ... }
    let run_in_background = args.get("run_in_background")...
    if run_in_background { ... } else {
        let cwd = std::env::current_dir()...;
        #[cfg(windows)] let output = { ... };
        #[cfg(not(windows))] let output = { ... };
        match output { Ok(output) => { ... if result.len() > 50000 { ... } ... }, Err(e) => ... }
    }
}
```
## Mandated refactor
1. Split into: `parse_bash_args(&HashMap) -> BashRequest`, `spawn_sync(cmd, cwd) -> Output`, `spawn_async(cmd) -> ShellId`, `render_output(output, max_len) -> String`.
2. Move OS-specific spawn logic into a `platform::spawn(cmd, cwd) -> io::Result<Output>` helper with separate `cfg` blocks at definition site, not at use site.
3. Replace the 50_000-char magic literal with a named const.
